londonGrill.description:
London Grill is a modern restaurant-bar web application with a full ordering cycle.

London Grill is a full-featured SPA for a restaurant-bar that demonstrates a comprehensive approach to building modern web interfaces. The project combines premium-style visual design with strong business logic: from a multi-level menu to authentication and order management.

Implemented functionality:

Dynamic menu system:
- multi-level tab navigation with drink categories (cocktails, infusions, wines, beer) and food categories (burgers, snacks);
- automatic item generation from assets folder structure via Vite glob imports;
- filtering by groups and subcategories with smooth transitions;
- product cards with images, prices, volumes, and add-to-cart button.

Complete cart and ordering flow:
- quantity management (increment/decrement);
- data persistence via localStorage with auto-sync;
- real-time total price calculation;
- table selection interface via custom dropdown;
- header cart indicator with badge counter.

Firebase authentication:
- sign-up and sign-in via email/password;
- protected routes (cart is available only for authorized users);
- real-time auth status tracking via onAuthStateChanged;
- logout button with current user email display.

Internationalization (i18n):
- EN/RU language switch without page reload;
- full UI localization via context provider;
- support for dynamic translations for auto-generated menu content.

Interactive events slider:
- custom promo slider with left/right navigation;
- smooth CSS slide transition animations;
- adaptive event cards with images and descriptions.

Landing page with hero section:
- large hero block with clear CTA elements;
- highlights section with key advantages;
- decorative elements (glow effects, patterns) for visual depth.

Notification system:
- ToastProvider for status messages (success, error, info);
- automatic hide via timeout;
- adaptive positioning for mobile devices.

Key technical solutions:

Architecture and state management:
- React with functional components and hooks;
- MobX for reactive global cart state management;
- Context API for i18n and toast system;
- React Router v6 with dynamic navigation and protected routes.

Styling and UX:
- CSS Modules for component-level style isolation;
- custom design system with CSS variables (sage/gold/warm palette);
- responsive design via media queries and flexible grid/flexbox layouts;
- smooth transitions and animations (fade, slide, hover effects);
- image optimization with lazy loading and async decoding.

Performance and optimization:
- Vite for instant HMR and optimized production builds;
- useMemo for caching heavy computations (dynamic menu generation);
- useCallback for memoizing event handlers;
- dynamic image imports via glob patterns.

Firebase integration:
- Firebase Authentication with email/password provider;
- secure config storage via environment variables (.env);
- auth error handling with user-facing notifications.

Code quality:
- ESLint for static code analysis;
- Prettier for consistent formatting;
- configured ignore files to exclude build artifacts.

Deployment:
- project is configured for automatic deployment via Vercel with SPA routing support;
- vercel.json configuration for correct client-side route handling;
- use of environment variables for sensitive Firebase data.

vinylStore.description:
Vinyl Haven is a full-stack vinyl marketplace (frontend part of a team project).

Vinyl Haven is a modern online platform for buying and selling vinyl records, built by a team for the CIS market. I was responsible for full frontend development, creating an intuitive interface with advanced features for both collectors and casual users. The project demonstrates teamwork, C#/.NET backend integration, and scalable enterprise-grade application development.

My contribution (Frontend Development):

Full UI/UX from scratch:
- built the frontend structure from initial setup to production-ready state;
- created an adaptive component system with a minimalist visual direction;
- implemented Header with dynamic navigation and user-state indicators;
- built Footer with multilingual links and clear information architecture.

Landing and informational pages:
- Home page as a complete pre-landing with hero section, featured collections, and CTA;
- About page describing project concept and platform advantages;
- Contact page with feedback forms;
- Policy page for privacy policy and user agreements.

Catalog and filtering system:
- interactive vinyl catalog with product cards;
- advanced filtering by genre, artist, release year, and price;
- detailed Card pages with full release information;
- backend API integration for dynamic data loading.

Authentication and role-based access:
- Login page with registration/login flows;
- role-based pages for buyer/seller/admin;
- protected routes with redirects based on authentication status;
- C# backend integration for JWT tokens and session management.

E-commerce functionality:
- shopping cart with quantity management;
- wishlist for saving interesting releases;
- integration with backend order-processing endpoints;
- order state tracking.

Internationalization (i18next):
- full EN/RU support via react-i18next;
- dynamic language switch with persistence in localStorage;
- localized JSON files for all interface text;
- SEO-friendly multilingual approach.

Theme system (Light/Dark Mode):
- theme switch between light and dark modes;
- persistent theme selection via localStorage;
- CSS variables for all color tokens;
- smooth transitions during theme changes;
- adaptation to user system preferences.

Animations and UX enhancements:
- CSS/SCSS animations for smooth state transitions;
- skeleton loaders for better perceived performance;
- scroll animations and entrance effects;
- hover states and micro-interactions for improved engagement.

Infinite Scroll:
- infinite catalog scrolling with lazy product loading;
- Intersection Observer API for element visibility detection;
- optimized rendering for large lists;
- loading indicators and error handling.

Backend integration (C# .NET API):
- configured all API endpoints for backend communication;
- worked with RESTful API via fetch/axios;
- handled async requests and error states;
- PostgreSQL integration through backend layer;
- Vite proxy setup for development and production;
- migration from local backend to production server (Railway);
- RTK Query refactoring for improved data fetching.

Key technical solutions:

TypeScript and type safety:
- full typing for components, props, and API responses;
- strict TypeScript configuration for early error detection;
- interfaces for domain models (VinylRecord, Customer, Order);
- typed Redux store and actions.

Redux Toolkit state management:
- centralized state management via RTK;
- RTK Query for efficient data fetching and caching;
- slices for cart, wishlist, and authentication;
- optimistic UI updates;
- automatic cache invalidation on changes.

SCSS and modular styling architecture:
- SCSS for advanced styling capabilities;
- breakpoint mixins for responsive design (@use './breakpoints');
- modular styling approach (text.scss, buttons.scss, inputs.scss);
- CSS custom properties for theming;
- mobile-first approach with adaptive components;
- utility classes for repeated patterns.

React Router v6 navigation:
- custom HistoryRouter for programmatic navigation;
- ScrollToTop component for scroll restoration;
- protected routes with role-based access control;
- lazy-loaded pages for code splitting.

Vite bundler configuration:
- optimized Vite configuration for dev and production;
- proxy setup for API requests in development;
- environment variables through loadEnv;
- auto-reload and HMR for faster development;
- production build optimization with minification.

Notification system:
- context provider for global notifications;
- toast notifications for user feedback;
- error boundary for graceful error handling.

Performance optimizations:
- lazy loading of components and routes;
- memoization via useMemo and useCallback;
- list virtualization for large catalogs;
- image optimization and lazy loading;
- route-based code splitting.

Cross-browser compatibility:
- ESLint configuration for code quality;
- support for modern and legacy browsers through Babel;
- accessibility best practices (jsx-a11y);
- React hooks rules via eslint-plugin-react-hooks.

Deployment and DevOps:
- production build setup with Vite;
- Railway integration for backend hosting;
- environment-based configuration (dev/prod);
- CORS setup for cross-origin requests;
- reverse proxy configuration for API;
- production issue debugging with source maps.

Team collaboration:
- teamwork using Git feature branches;
- code reviews and pull request workflow;
- synchronization with backend developers on API contracts;
- documentation for components and API integrations;
- adherence to coding standards and best practices.

Important:
- backend server is currently unavailable, so some online features may not work in the demo.

pet.description:
Pet Care Project is a TypeScript/SCSS landing page built with a mobile-first approach.

