Pure CSS Architecture (51%):
- no CSS-in-JS or preprocessors, pure CSS only;
- modern CSS features (CSS Grid, Flexbox, Custom Properties);
- dedicated styles/ directory for modular organization;
- CSS modules or BEM methodology usage;
- cross-browser compatibility without extra dependencies.

TypeScript Integration (47%):
- strict typing for all interactive components;
- type-safe event handlers and DOM manipulations;
- separate tsconfig.json and tsconfig.node.json configurations;
- TypeScript used for build scripts and tooling.

Product Showcase Features:
- hero section with product visualization;
- product specs and characteristics;
- image gallery with interactive elements;
- call-to-action blocks for conversion.

Modern Development Setup:
- Vite as an ultra-fast bundler;
- ESLint for code quality and consistency;
- hot module replacement for fast development;
- optimized production build with minification.

Key technical solutions:

Vanilla CSS Mastery:
- CSS Custom Properties for theming;
- CSS Grid for complex layouts;
- Flexbox for flexible components;
- media queries for responsive breakpoints;
- CSS animations without JavaScript overhead;
- progressive enhancement approach.

TypeScript Configuration:
- strict typing via tsconfig.json;
- separate config for Node.js scripts (tsconfig.node.json);
- ES module output for modern browsers;
- strict mode for maximum type safety.

Vite Build System:
- custom vite.config.ts configuration;
- asset optimization and code splitting;
- dev server with instant HMR;
- production build with tree-shaking.

Project Structure:
- clear src/ separation for source code;
- styles/ for CSS modules and global styles;
- public/ for static assets (images, fonts);
- modular architecture for scalability.

Code Quality:
- ESLint configuration for TypeScript;
- consistent code style;
- automated linting in development workflow;
- pre-commit hooks for code quality.

Performance Optimization:
- minimal JavaScript for better performance;
- CSS-only animations where possible;
- lazy loading of images;
- optimized assets via Vite;
- small bundle size due to no heavy libraries.

Responsive Images:
- adaptive images via picture element;
- optimization for different screen densities (1x, 2x);
- WebP with JPEG/PNG fallback;
- lazy loading for above-the-fold content.

Deployment:
- Vercel setup through vercel.json;
- SPA routing configuration;
- optimized production build;
- automatic deployment on push to main branch;
- environment-based configuration.

Approach advantages:

Vanilla CSS Benefits:
- zero runtime dependencies for styles;
- maximum performance;
- full styling control without abstractions;
- smaller bundle size;
- better understanding of CSS fundamentals.

TypeScript Safety:
- early error detection;
- improved developer experience with autocomplete;
- self-documenting code via types;
- safer refactoring.

Mobile-First Advantages:
- better performance on mobile devices;
- progressive enhancement for desktop;
- forced prioritization of important content;
- improved accessibility.

nike.description:
Nike Product Slider is an interactive web component that showcases a modern product slider inspired by premium brand design. The project demonstrates a strong understanding of building visually engaging user interfaces with smooth animations and responsive behavior.

Implemented functionality:
- full-screen slider using CSS viewport-relative units (100vw / 100vh);
- smooth transitions between slides with autoplay support;
- manual navigation via left/right arrow controls;
- layered typography effects (filled + outlined text) for visual depth;
- animated shadows and floating effects for product images;
- interactive rating system (stars) with fill logic up to the selected position;
- functional BUY NOW button with a dynamic cart counter;
- adaptive layout for all device sizes with dedicated breakpoints.

Key technical solutions:
- responsiveness: CSS Grid and Flexbox are used to create a flexible layout that adapts to any screen size;
- performance: Vite provides fast builds and optimized asset loading;
- UX: smooth CSS transitions and animations deliver natural interactions without lag;
- state management: JavaScript logic controls current slide, counters, and animation states.

Deployment:
 project is configured for automatic deployment to GitHub Pages via npm scripts.

energo.description:
Energy Construction is an HTML landing page with Owl Carousel and SVG iconography.

